      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Everything looks correct in the database:\n\n1. **Appointment type id=1**: `name='Discovery Consultation'`, `published=True`, `staff=[2]` ✅\n2. **Invite id=2** (short_code `27e80afd`): `staff_user_ids=[2]`, `appointment_type_ids=[1]` ✅\n3. **Invite id=1** (short_code `539f5a8f`): also has `staff_user_ids=[2]` ✅\n\nBoth URLs are correctly configured. The data is all correct in the DB.\n\nThe only issue is the QWeb cache on the public-facing website. Let me now do the aggressive cache bust:\n1. Archive/unarchive view 1117 (already done in first script)\n2. Touch all the appointment-related views to force recompilation\n3. Also try to modify the view arch with a space change to force re-render\n\nActually, the most reliable approach for Odoo SaaS is to edit the arch_db of the view that renders the H1 (view 1117). Let me add a whitespace and remove it to force recompilation.\n\nAlso, let me try the web controller approach - maybe I can call `website.clear_caches()` or similar.\n\nLet me write the final comprehensive script.",
      "timestamp": 1782280332129
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "write",
      "code": "{\"content\": \"import xmlrpc.client\\nimport ssl\\nimport time\\n\\nURL = \\\"https://andiekobbie.odoo.com\\\"\\nDB = \\\"andiekobbie\\\"\\nAPI_KEY = \\\"4a4b79c4fa6716a3f294cb7279b24105218906d5\\\"\\nUSERNAME = \\\"andiekobbietks@outlook.com\\\"\\n\\nssl_ctx = ssl.create_default_context()\\ncommon = xmlrpc.client.ServerProxy(f\\\"{URL}/xmlrpc/2/common\\\", context=ssl_ctx)\\nmodels = xmlrpc.client.ServerProxy(f\\\"{URL}/xmlrpc/2/object\\\", context=ssl_ctx)\\n\\nuid = common.authenticate(DB, USERNAME, API_KEY, {})\\nprint(f\\\"Authenticated: uid={uid}\\\")\\n\\ndef execute(model, method, args=None, kwargs=None):\\n    a = args or []\\n    k = kwargs or {}\\n    return models.execute_kw(DB, uid, API_KEY, model, method, a, k)\\n\\n# 1. View 1117 - read current arch, do a whitespace change to force recompile\\nprint(\\\"--- View 1117 arch modification ---\\\")\\nview = execute(\\\"ir.ui.view\\\", \\\"read\\\", [[1117], [\\\"arch_db\\\"]])\\narch = view[0][\\\"arch_db\\\"]\\nprint(f\\\"  Current arch (first 200 chars): {arch[:200]}\\\")\\n\\n# Write a space at the end of the arch to trigger recompilation\\nnew_arch = arch.rstrip() + \\\" \\\\n\\\"\\nexecute(\\\"ir.ui.view\\\", \\\"write\\\", [[1117], {\\\"arch_db\\\": new_arch}])\\nprint(\\\"  Wrote arch with trailing space\\\")\\ntime.sleep(1)\\n\\n# Now write back the clean version\\nclean_arch = arch.rstrip() + \\\"\\\\n\\\"\\nexecute(\\\"ir.ui.view\\\", \\\"write\\\", [[1117], {\\\"arch_db\\\": clean_arch}])\\nprint(\\\"  Wrote arch back to clean\\\")\\ntime.sleep(1)\\n\\n# 2. Also archive/unarchive view 3328 (the other \\\"Appointment: Appointment Info\\\")\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n--- Touching view 3328 ---\\\")\\nexecute(\\\"ir.ui.view\\\", \\\"write\\\", [[3328], {\\\"active\\\": False}])\\nprint(\\\"  Archived 3328\\\")\\ntime.sleep(0.5)\\nexecute(\\\"ir.ui.view\\\", \\\"write\\\", [[3328], {\\\"active\\\": True}])\\nprint(\\\"  Unarchived 3328\\\")\\n\\n# 3. Touch parent view 1118 (\\\"Appointment\\\") too\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n--- Touching view 1118 (parent) ---\\\")\\nexecute(\\\"ir.ui.view\\\", \\\"write\\\", [[1118], {\\\"active\\\": False}])\\nprint(\\\"  Archived 1118\\\")\\ntime.sleep(0.5)\\nexecute(\\\"ir.ui.view\\\", \\\"write\\\", [[1118], {\\\"active\\\": True}])\\nprint(\\\"  Unarchived 1118\\\")\\n\\n# 4. Try to call website cache clear\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n--- Attempting website cache clear ---\\\")\\ntry:\\n    # Try using ir.module.module to trigger registry reload\\n    result = execute(\\\"ir.module.module\\\", \\\"search\\\", [[[\\\"name\\\", \\\"=\\\", \\\"website\\\"]]])\\n    if result:\\n        print(f\\\"  Found website module: id={result[0]}\\\")\\nexcept Exception as e:\\n    print(f\\\"  Module search failed: {e}\\\")\\n\\n# 5. Try to force write on ir.qweb via base model\\ntry:\\n    # Try clear cache via website model\\n    result = execute(\\\"website\\\", \\\"search\\\", [[]])\\n    if result:\\n        print(f\\\"  Found website: id={result[0]}\\\")\\nexcept Exception as e:\\n    print(f\\\"  Website search failed: {e}\\\")\\n\\n# 6. Re-verify the appointment type\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n--- Final verification ---\\\")\\napt = execute(\\\"appointment.type\\\", \\\"read\\\", [[1], [\\\"name\\\", \\\"is_published\\\", \\\"website_published\\\", \\\"message_intro\\\", \\\"message_confirmation\\\"]])\\na = apt[0]\\nprint(f\\\"  name='{a['name']}'\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"  website_published={a.get('website_published')}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"  is_published={a.get('is_published')}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"  message_intro (first 100): {str(a.get('message_intro', ''))[:100]}\\\")\\n\\n# 7. Verify invite\\ninvite = execute(\\\"appointment.invite\\\", \\\"read\\\", [[2], [\\\"short_code\\\", \\\"staff_user_ids\\\", \\\"appointment_type_ids\\\"]])\\ni = invite[0]\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\n  Invite short_code='{i['short_code']}'\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"  staff_user_ids={i['staff_user_ids']}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"  appointment_type_ids={i['appointment_type_ids']}\\\")\\n\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n=== DONE ===\\\")\\nprint(\\\"All DB data is correct. Cache bust via arch edit + view toggling done.\\\")\\nprint(\\\"If H1 still shows old name, the SaaS CDN may need up to 1h to expire.\\\")\\nprint(\\\"Try opening the page in an incognito/private window.\\\")\\n\", \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Documents\\\\fix_odoo_cache3.py\"}",
