      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\AKcloud\\akcloud-deploy\\DESIGN.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: version: alpha\n3: name: AndieKobbieTech Solutions\n4: description: >\n5:   Phosphorescent circuit board aesthetic for a UK sovereign cloud architect\n6:   and Microsoft Solutions Partner consultant. Dark matter surfaces with\n7:   fluorescent neon green electrical charge running through every interaction.\n8: \n9: colors:\n10:   primary: \"#39FF14\"\n11:   on-primary: \"#080808\"\n12:   primary-dim: \"#1FCC00\"\n13:   primary-mute: \"rgba(57, 255, 20, 0.12)\"\n14:   secondary: \"#FFFFFF\"\n15:   tertiary: \"#191919\"\n16:   neutral: \"#080808\"\n17:   surface-1: \"#111111\"\n18:   surface-2: \"#191919\"\n19:   border: \"#242424\"\n20:   text-hi: \"#C8C8C8\"\n21:   text-mid: \"#787878\"\n22:   text-lo: \"#3A3A3A\"\n23: \n24: typography:\n25:   display:\n26:     fontFamily: Exo 2\n27:     fontSize: 4.5rem\n28:     fontWeight: 900\n29:     letterSpacing: 0.01em\n30:     lineHeight: 1.0\n31:   h1:\n32:     fontFamily: Exo 2\n33:     fontSize: 3rem\n34:     fontWeight: 700\n35:     letterSpacing: 0.01em\n36:     lineHeight: 1.1\n37:   h2:\n38:     fontFamily: Exo 2\n39:     fontSize: 2.25rem\n40:     fontWeight: 700\n41:     letterSpacing: 0.01em\n42:     lineHeight: 1.15\n43:   h3:\n44:     fontFamily: Exo 2\n45:     fontSize: 1.5rem\n46:     fontWeight: 600\n47:     lineHeight: 1.25\n48:   body-lg:\n49:     fontFamily: DM Sans\n50:     fontSize: 1.125rem\n51:     fontWeight: 400\n52:     lineHeight: 1.6\n53:   body-md:\n54:     fontFamily: DM Sans\n55:     fontSize: 1rem\n56:     fontWeight: 400\n57:     lineHeight: 1.65\n58:   body-sm:\n59:     fontFamily: DM Sans\n60:     fontSize: 0.875rem\n61:     fontWeight: 400\n62:     lineHeight: 1.6\n63:   label:\n64:     fontFamily: Exo 2\n65:     fontSize: 0.75rem\n66:     fontWeight: 700\n67:     letterSpacing: 0.1em\n68:     lineHeight: 1.0\n69:   mono:\n70:     fontFamily: JetBrains Mono\n71:     fontSize: 0.875rem\n72:     fontWeight: 400\n73:     lineHeight: 1.5\n74: \n75: rounded:\n76:   sm: 2px\n77:   md: 4px\n78:   lg: 8px\n79:   full: 0px\n80: \n81: spacing:\n82:   xs: 4px\n83:   sm: 8px\n84:   md: 16px\n85:   lg: 24px\n86:   xl: 48px\n87:   2xl: 96px\n88: \n89: components:\n90:   button-primary:\n91:     backgroundColor: \"{colors.primary}\"\n92:     textColor: \"{colors.on-primary}\"\n93:     typography: \"{typography.label}\"\n94:     rounded: \"{rounded.md}\"\n95:     padding: 14px 28px\n96:     shadow: \"0 0 8px #39FF14, 0 0 24px rgba(57,255,20,0.50), 0 0 48px rgba(57,255,20,0.25)\"\n97:   button-primary-hover:\n98:     backgroundColor: \"{colors.primary}\"\n99:     shadow: \"0 0 12px #39FF14, 0 0 32px rgba(57,255,20,0.55), 0 0 72px rgba(57,255,20,0.28), 0 0 120px rgba(57,255,20,0.12)\"\n100:     transform: translateY(-1px)\n101:   button-ghost:\n102:     backgroundColor: transparent\n103:     textColor: \"{colors.secondary}\"\n104:     typography: \"{typography.label}\"\n105:     rounded: \"{rounded.md}\"\n106:     padding: 13px 27px\n107:     border: \"1px solid {colors.border}\"\n108:   button-ghost-hover:\n109:     textColor: \"{colors.primary}\"\n110:     border: \"1px solid {colors.primary}\"\n111:     shadow: \"inset 0 0 0 1px {colors.primary}, 0 0 6px #39FF14, 0 0 14px rgba(57,255,20,0.55)\"\n112:   service-card:\n113:     backgroundColor: \"{colors.surface-1}\"\n114:     border: \"1px solid {colors.border}\"\n115:     rounded: \"{rounded.lg}\"\n116:     padding: 32px\n117:   service-card-hover:\n118:     border: \"1px solid rgba(57,255,20,0.30)\"\n119:     shadow: \"0 0 0 1px rgba(57,255,20,0.15), 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.40)\"\n120:   ms-badge:\n121:     backgroundColor: \"{colors.surface-1}\"\n122:     border: \"1px solid {colors.border}\"\n123:     rounded: \"{rounded.lg}\"\n124:     padding: 16px 24px\n125:   nav:\n126:     backgroundColor: \"rgba(8,8,8,0.85)\"\n127:     border-bottom: \"1px solid {colors.border}\"\n128:     height: 64px\n129:     backdrop-filter: blur(12px)\n130:   nav-link:\n131:     textColor: \"{colors.text-hi}\"\n132:     typography: \"{typography.label}\"\n133:   nav-link-active:\n134:     textColor: \"{colors.secondary}\"\n135:     indicator-shadow: \"0 0 6px #39FF14, 0 0 14px rgba(57,255,20,0.55)\"\n136: ---\n137: \n138: ## Overview\n139: \n140: Phosphorescent circuit board meets sovereign infrastructure.\n141: \n142: AndieKobbieTech Solutions is the technical authority for UK organisations\n143: navigating Microsoft's partner ecosystem, hybrid cloud architecture, and\n144: digital sovereignty. The UI should feel like being inside the infrastructure\n145: itself — dark matter with electrical charge escaping through the traces.\n146: \n147: The fluorescent green (`#39FF14`) is not decorative. It is the charge carrier.\n148: It appears only on interactive elements, key brand moments, and live system\n149: indicators — never as background fill, never diluted. The contrast between\n150: near-absolute black surfaces and the phosphorescent green is what makes the\n151: brand feel genuinely lit rather than styled.\n152: \n153: Target audience: founders, IT leads, and arts/public sector organisations\n154: in the UK. The tone is precise, direct, and confident — the voice of someone\n155: who builds the infrastructure rather than sells a slide deck about it.\n156: \n157: ## Colors\n158: \n159: - **Primary (`#39FF14`):** Fluorescent neon green — the sole driver for all\n160:   interaction. CTAs, active nav states, hover indicators, circuit traces.\n161:   Carries a layered glow shadow at all times to simulate phosphorescent pigment\n162:   under reflected light. Never use as a background fill — it must always appear\n163:   as a light source against dark surfaces, not a colour block.\n164: - **On-Primary (`#080808`):** Black text rendered on green buttons and badges.\n165:   Ensures WCAG AA contrast on the primary colour.\n166: - **Primary-Dim (`#1FCC00`):** Pressed/active state for green elements.\n167:   Slightly darker to signal depression without losing the neon quality.\n168: - **Primary-Mute (`rgba(57,255,20,0.12)`):** Tinted panel background for hover\n169:   states on cards and menu items. Barely perceptible — implies the green\n170:   without overwhelming the surface.\n171: - **Secondary (`#FFFFFF`):** Pure white — used for \"ANDIE\", \"TECH.\", all\n172:   display headings, and primary body text. One half of the brand name split.\n173: - **Neutral (`#080808`):** Near-absolute black. Page background. Not pure black\n174:   (`#000000`) — this retains a subtle warmth that prevents the background from\n175:   feeling printed.\n176: - **Surface-1 (`#111111`):** Primary content panels and cards. Distinguishable\n177:   from the page background only in direct comparison.\n178: - **Surface-2 (`#191919`):** Elevated surfaces — nav, modals, dropdown menus.\n179:   The topmost visible layer before the green appears.\n180: - **Border (`#242424`):** All dividing lines, card borders, input outlines.\n181:   Subtle enough not to create a grid, present enough to define structure.\n182: - **Text-Hi (`#C8C8C8`):** Secondary body copy, card descriptions, supporting\n183:   content. Warm mid-grey — not cold.\n184: - **Text-Mid (`#787878`):** Captions, metadata, timestamps, legal text.\n185: - **Text-Lo (`#3A3A3A`):** Disabled states, placeholder text, decorative labels.\n186: \n187: ## Typography\n188: \n189: Three families. Each has a specific role and must not be substituted.\n190: \n191: - **Exo 2 (Display + Headings + Labels):** Geometric, technical, infrastructure-\n192:   native. Used at weight 900 for display and brand text, 700 for section\n193:   headings, 600 for sub-headings, 700 uppercase for all labels and button copy.\n194:   Pairs the circuit board aesthetic with human legibility. Import from Google\n195:   Fonts.\n196: - **DM Sans (Body):** Warm geometric sans. Human-readable at all sizes without\n197:   feeling corporate. Used exclusively for paragraph copy, card descriptions,\n198:   form fields. Never for headings or interactive labels.\n199: - **JetBrains Mono (Data + Code):** Used for technical specifications, ADR\n200:   reference numbers, Microsoft Partner IDs, stack names, version strings, and\n201:   any numerical data that needs to read as a system output rather than prose.\n202: \n203: Brand name typographic rule — consistent across all display contexts:\n204:   `ANDIE` → Secondary (#FFFFFF), weight 900\n205:   `KOBBIE` → Primary (#39FF14), weight 900, glow-sm shadow\n206:   `TECH.` → Secondary (#FFFFFF), weight 900\n207: The trailing period is not punctuation — it is part of the brand mark.\n208: \n209: ## Layout\n210: \n211: 12-column grid. Max content width 1280px. Base spacing unit 8px.\n212: \n213: Desktop section vertical rhythm: 96px top and bottom padding.\n214: Mobile section vertical rhythm: 64px top and bottom padding.\n215: \n216: Navigation bar: fixed, 64px height, full viewport width, backdrop blur.\n217: Hero: full viewport height, content vertically centred at 40% from top.\n218: Content sections: alternating single-column text and three-column card grids.\n219: Maximum readable line length for body text: 72 characters (approximately 680px).\n220: \n221: Background texture: a 48×48px repeating circuit grid at 3% green opacity\n222: overlaid on the neutral background. Visible only when looked for — ambient\n223: context, not decoration.\n224: \n225: ## Elevation & Depth\n226: \n227: Depth is conveyed through glow, not shadow.\n228: \n229: Traditional box shadows are not used in this system. Surfaces are\n230: distinguished from each other by their background colour tokens\n231: (neutral → surface-1 → surface-2 → border). No drop shadows appear\n232: between stacked elements.\n233: \n234: The single exception: the glow system applied to interactive elements\n235: in the primary colour. Three intensity levels:\n236: \n237: - **Glow-SM:** `0 0 6px #39FF14, 0 0 14px rgba(57,255,20,0.55)`\n238:   Applied to interactive green elements at rest and to the AK logomark\n239:   circuit traces. The near-field phosphorescence.\n240: - **Glow-MD:** `0 0 8px #39FF14, 0 0 24px rgba(57,255,20,0.50), 0 0 48px rgba(57,255,20,0.25)`\n241:   Applied on hover. The mid-diffusion layer — as if the surface has\n242:   warmed under light.\n243: - **Glow-LG:** `0 0 12px #39FF14, 0 0 32px rgba(57,255,20,0.55), 0 0 72px rgba(57,255,20,0.28), 0 0 120px rgba(57,255,20,0.12)`\n244:   Applied on active/focus and to the primary CTA button at rest. Maximum\n245:   ambient spread — a UV source illuminating the immediate area.\n246: \n247: Apply glow only to elements rendered in the primary colour. Static text,\n248: body copy, and decorative elements carry no glow — restraint here is\n249: what makes the lit elements feel electrically charged by contrast.\n250: \n251: ## Shapes\n252: \n253: Architectural precision. Minimal radius, no pill shapes.\n254: \n255: All interactive elements: `rounded-md` (4px). Just enough softness to\n256: feel contemporary — insufficient to feel friendly or rounded. This is\n257: infrastructure, not consumer software.\n258: \n259: Cards and panels: `rounded-lg` (8px). Slightly more generous to\n260: distinguish containers from controls.\n261: \n262: No `border-radius: 9999px` (pill) shapes anywhere in the system.\n263: No circular avatar frames (use 4px radius square crops).\n264: \n265: Service cards carry a circuit corner accent — a two-sided green border\n266: bracket in the top-left corner that expands on hover (from 40×40px to\n267: 80×80px), carrying the glow-sm shadow. This is the signature micro-\n268: interaction of the brand. It is built with a `::before` pseudo-element,\n269: not a separate DOM element.\n270: \n271: ## Components\n272: \n273: **Button — Primary**\n274: Green fill, black text, uppercase label typography, 4px radius, 14px×28px\n275: padding, glow-md shadow at rest, glow-lg on hover, translateY(-1px) on hover.\n276: The primary CTA reads: `BOOK A CONSULTATION`.\n277: \n278: **Button — Ghost**\n279: Transparent, white text, 1px border in `{colors.border}`, same sizing as\n280: primary. On hover: border transitions to primary green, text transitions to\n281: primary green, inset glow-sm shadow appears. Used for secondary actions\n282: (`SEE THE STACK →`, `VIEW ARCHITECTURE →`).\n283: \n284: **Service Card**\n285: Surface-1 background, border in `{colors.border}`, 8px radius, 32px padding.\n286: Circuit corner accent in primary green (::before pseudo-element, top-left).\n287: On hover: border colour transitions to `rgba(57,255,20,0.30)`, outer glow\n288: appears (`0 0 0 1px rgba(57,255,20,0.15), 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.40)`),\n289: corner accent expands and brightens to glow-md.\n290: \n291: **Microsoft Partner Badge**\n292: Surface-1 background, border, 8px radius, 16px×24px padding. Microsoft logo\n293: at 20px height (official lockup). Track name (`Data & AI`, `Digital & App\n294: Innovation`) in primary green, label typography, glow-sm shadow.\n295: \n296: **Navigation**\n297: Fixed, 64px height, 85% opacity neutral background with 12px backdrop blur,\n298: 1px bottom border. Logo on left. Nav links centred or right-aligned. Primary\n299: CTA button always visible on right. Nav links in label typography (uppercase,\n300: 0.1em tracking). Active state: white text, 2px underline in primary with\n301: glow-sm, animated via `::after` pseudo-element width transition.\n302: \n303: **Circuit Horizontal Rule**\n304: Replaces all `<hr>` dividers between sections. A 1px line in `{colors.border}`\n305: with an animated green pulse travelling left to right over 3 seconds, infinite.\n306: The pulse is 20% of the rule width, gradient-faded at both ends, carrying\n307: glow-md. Optional node dots (6px circles, primary green, glow-sm) at section\n308: junctions. Animation respects `prefers-reduced-motion`.\n309: \n310: **Section Label (Eyebrow)**\n311: Label typography, primary green, glow-sm text-shadow, uppercase. Appears\n312: above every section heading. Never used as a standalone element — always\n313: paired with an `h2` or `h3` below it.\n314: \n315: ## Do's and Don'ts\n316: \n317: - **Do** apply the primary green exclusively to interactive or key brand\n318:   elements. Never use it as a background fill or decorative band.\n319: - **Do** keep the KOBBIE portion of the brand name in primary green in all\n320:   display contexts — hero, nav, footer, og:image.\n321: - **Do** include the trailing period in `ANDIEKOBBITECH.` in all display uses.\n322: - **Do** render all technical identifiers (partner IDs, ADR numbers, stack\n323:   names, version strings) in JetBrains Mono at body-sm size.\n324: - **Do** maintain WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1) on all text. On-primary (#080808)\n325:   on primary (#39FF14) passes at 10.6:1. White on surface-1 passes at 15.8:1.\n326: - **Do** respect `prefers-reduced-motion` — disable all animations including\n327:   the circuit trace pulse when the user has requested reduced motion.\n328: - **Don't** use more than two font weights on a single screen section.\n329: - **Don't** use `border-radius` values larger than `rounded-lg` (8px) on any\n330:   element. No pill shapes, no full-circle crops.\n331: - **Don't** apply glow effects to body copy, paragraph text, or static labels.\n332:   Glow is reserved for interactive and primary brand elements only.\n333: - **Don't** render the green on any background lighter than `{colors.surface-2}`\n334:   (#191919). The glow effect requires dark contrast — on light surfaces it\n335:   reads as saturated lime, not phosphorescent charge.\n336: - **Don't** add decorative gradients to background surfaces. Gradients appear\n337:   only inside the animated circuit trace and the primary-mute hover tint.\n338: - **Don't** use numbered section markers (01 / 02 / 03) — the content sections\n339:   are not a sequential process and numbering would misrepresent the structure.\n340: - **Don't** place more than one primary CTA per screen section.\n\n(End of file - total 340 lines)\n</content>",
      "status": "success",
