    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "To answer your questions:\n\n**1. No, you don't need the Website app.** The Odoo `appointment` module works standalone. Your booking pages live at `/book/27e80afd` and `/appointment/discovery-consultation-1` — those are served by the appointment module's own controllers, not the Website app. The Website app just adds website builder/editor features on top.\n\n**2. Theme matching** — The Odoo appointment page uses Odoo's own frontend styling (white/blue default). You can't easily restyle it to match your AKcloud dark theme (#080808 bg, #39FF14 green, Exo 2 fonts) without either:\n- **Custom CSS in Odoo** (Website app → Edit → HTML/CSS injection)\n- **Embed via iframe** on your Netlify site with a styled wrapper\n- **Redirect** the \"Book a Consultation\" button to the Odoo booking URL (which your site already does — the `openBooking()` function checks `localStorage.getItem('ak_booking_url')`)\n\n**3. Netlify credentials** — The admin panel is at `/admin.html` with default login `admin`/`admin` (hardcoded in `index.html:674`). The Odoo connection config (URL, DB, user, API key) is stored in **localStorage per-device** — not in the repo. Your Netlify environment variables (RESEND_API_KEY, etc.) are set in the Netlify dashboard, not in code.\n\n**Your setup is already correct:** \"Book a Consultation\" → checks `ak_booking_url` in localStorage → opens your Odoo booking link. Set that URL in the admin panel to `https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/book/27e80afd` and it'll open directly.",
      "timestamp": 1782280716665
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have a clear picture. Let me understand what the user is asking:\n\n1. **\"Do I need the Website app to have the appointment page showing?\"** - They're asking if they need Odoo's Website app module installed to use the appointment booking page.\n\n2. **\"I need to follow the same theme as my site\"** - They want the Odoo appointment page to match their AKcloud theme (dark, #39FF14 green, Exo 2/DM Sans fonts).\n\n3. **\"You find credentials to control it since it's being pushed to netlify here\"** - They want me to find credentials for their Netlify site.\n\nLooking at the admin.html, I can see there's an admin panel with:\n- Odoo config section (URL, DB, user, API key) - stored in localStorage\n- Booking URL config - stored in localStorage\n- Waitlist management - stored in localStorage\n\nThe credentials for the admin panel are in the JavaScript at the bottom of index.html. Let me decode the base64 strings:\n- `atob('L2FkbWluLmh0bWw=')` = `/admin.html`\n- `atob('YW5kaWVrb2JiaWU=')` = `andiekobbie`\n\nAnd the auth check: `ok:function(u,p){var s=_ld();return s.ph?s.ph===_h(u+':'+p):(u==='admin'&&p==='admin');}`\n\nSo the default credentials are `admin`/`admin` if no password hash is stored.\n\nThe user's Odoo credentials are stored in localStorage on the admin panel, not hardcoded. The API key they provided (`4a4b79c4fa6716a3f294cb7279b24105218906d5`) is for their Odoo instance.\n\nNow, for the actual questions:\n\n**1. Do they need the Website app?**\n\n\nThe appointment module operates independently from the Website app—they can embed booking pages via iframe or link directly to Odoo's appointment URLs without requiring the Website module. **2. Theme matching** - Odoo's appointment pages use their own styling, so they'd need to customize the template to align with their AKcloud design.\n\n**3. Netlify credentials** - The admin panel defaults to admin/admin, though the Odoo connection details are stored client-side in localStorage rather than in the repository. I should verify whether Netlify environment variables are configured, but I don't have direct access to check those settings.",
      "timestamp": 1782280725145
    },
