0;`\n\nThe issue is that `#spx-presents` clips the content. When the wordmark is very wide on certain screens, it gets clipped. And the `max-width: 95vw` might be too restrictive.\n\nLet me fix this by:\n1. Removing `overflow: hidden` from `#spx-presents` - the `#spx` already has `overflow: hidden`\n2. Keeping the mobile media query for smaller font sizes\n3. Making sure the typewriter width is correct for \"presents\" (8 characters)\n\nFor \"presents\" at the font size, 8.2em should be enough. Let me check... \"presents\" is 8 characters. At JetBrains Mono, each character is roughly the same width. 8.2em should work. But maybe the letter-spacing of 0.55em is adding extra width. Let me recalculate.\n\n\"presents\" = 8 chars × (1ch + 0.55em letter-spacing) ≈ 8 × 1.55em = 12.4em. But the last character shouldn't have trailing letter-spacing, so it's more like 7 × 1.55em + 1em = 11.85em. So `width: 8.2em` is definitely too small!\n\nLet me fix the typewriter width. For 8 characters with 0.55em letter-spacing:\n- Each char + spacing = ~1.55em\n- 8 chars = 8 × 1ch = 8em base\n- 7 inter-character spacings = 7 × 0.55em = 3.85em\n- Total ≈ 11.85em\n\nBut `letter-spacing` applies after every character including the last, so:\n- 8 × (1ch + 0.55em) ≈ 12.4em\n\nLet me set it to about 12em to be safe.\n\nActually wait, looking at the screenshot more carefully, \"presents\" does seem to show fully on desktop. The user might be talking about the mobile view. Let me focus on:\n\n1. Fix the `#spx-presents` overflow\n2. Fix the typewriter width\n3. Don't push to avoid burning more Netlify credits\n\nActually, the user said \"ensure u dont affect the site going offline\" and \"pls do tell me what i can do in case its too risky\". They're concerned about Netlify credits running out. I should:\n1. Make the CSS fix\n2. NOT push automatically\n3. Tell them to upgrade Netlify or wait for credits to reset\n4. Let them decide when to push\n\nActually, looking at the Netlify dashboard, it shows \"andiekobbietks's team has run out of credits\" and \"Your sites may go offline and production deploys and Agent Runners are currently disabled.\" This means:\n- The site may go offline\n- Production deploys are disabled\n- They need to upgrade\n\nBut looking at the deploy history, the latest deploy at 7:18 AM did publish successfully (master@4a67961). So it seems like deploys are still working for now.\n\nThe user is asking me to fix the presents display issue AND be careful not to break the site. I should:\n1. Fix the CSS\n2. Commit but NOT push\n3. Tell them to upgrade Netlify first, then push when ready\n\nLet me do that.",
