      "text": "Yes — **Netlify CLI** deploys directly from your machine, bypassing GitHub entirely:\n\n```bash\n# Install once\nnpm install -g netlify-cli\n\n# Login (opens browser)\nnetlify login\n\n# Deploy from your local folder\ncd C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\AKcloud\\akcloud-deploy\nnetlify deploy --prod --dir=.\n```\n\nThis pushes your files straight to `akcloud.netlify.app` — no GitHub, no build pipeline, no credits burned on CI. Your local files become the live site instantly.\n\n**Other options:**\n- **Drag-and-drop**: Go to https://app.netlify.com → your site → Deploys → drag the `akcloud-deploy` folder onto the page\n- **Netlify Dashboard editor**: Limited to HTML/CSS/JS edits in browser (Site editor → Pages)\n\nThe CLI is the fastest for your workflow — edit locally, `netlify deploy --prod`, done.",
