      "output": "Title: n8n Workflow Automation Cheat Sheet | 1337skills\nURL: https://1337skills.com/cheatsheets/n8n/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nn8n Workflow Automation Cheat Sheet | 1337skills Skip to content\n...\n# n8n Workflow Automation Cheat Sheet\n...\n📋 Copy All Commands 📄 Generate PDF\n...\n## Installation and\n...\n## Core Concepts\n...\n## Basic Workflow Creation\n...\nn8n\n...\nEnter a name for\n...\n### Adding and Connecting Nodes\n...\n”+”\n...\ndesired node type\n3.\n...\nthe node’s\n...\n4. Connect nodes by dragging from the output dot of one node to the input dot of another\n5. Click “\n...\n### Basic Workflow Example\n...\n## Triggers and Scheduling\n...\n### Trigger on File Changes\n...\n## Data Manipulation\n...\n### Function Node\n...\n### Split In Batches Node\n...\n### Merge Node\n...\n## Error Handling and Flow Control\n...\n### IF Node\n...\n### Switch Node\n...\n### Wait Node\n...\n## Working with APIs\n...\n### OAuth Authentication\n...\n### Webhook Response Node\n...\n## Database Operations\n...\n### MongoDB Node\n...\n## File Operations\n...\nRead Binary Files\n...\n### Write Binary File Node\n...\n### CSV Node\n...\n## AI Integration\n...\n### AI Document Processing\n...\n// Document processing\n...\n## Advanced Features\n...\n### Rate Limiting\n...\n## Deployment and Production\n...\nThis comprehensive n8n cheat sheet provides everything needed to build sophisticated workflow automations. From basic setup to advanced production deployment patterns, use these examples and best practices to create powerful, flexible automation workflows with n8n’s versatile platform.\n\n---\n\nTitle: I made an n8n Cheat Sheet! - Docs & Tutorials - n8n Community\nURL: https://community.n8n.io/t/i-made-an-n8n-cheat-sheet/100548\nPublished: 2025-04-13T07:15:50.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nI made an n8n Cheat Sheet! - Docs & Tutorials - n8n Community\n\n# I made an n8n Cheat Sheet!\n\nGetting Started with n8n Docs & Tutorials\n\ndata.popcorn April 13, 2025, 7:15am 1\n\nHi n8n community I created an n8n cheat sheet and wanted to share it with you all! It includes the following topics: • Getting Started with Triggers • Expressions • Built-in Nodes • Docker Self-Hosting • AI Agents • HTTP Requests • Keyboard Shortcuts • Common Node Settings\n\nI focused on summarizing the things I personally find easy to forget or frequently need to look up. Feel free to share your thoughts! If you spot any mistakes or have suggestions for what else to include, I’d really appreciate your feedback.\n\nThe high-res PDF version is available here.\n\n74 Likes\n\nbartv April 13, 2025, 11:16am 2\n\nThis is super nice, thanks for sharing! Perhaps you can share as a PDF? That’ll be a bit higher quality.\n\n2 Likes\n\ndata.popcorn April 13, 2025, 11:29am 3\n\nGot it. Here it is! n8n_cheatsheet_v1_pdf\n\n6 Likes\n\nJade April 13, 2025, 11:47am 4\n\nNice work@data.popcorn!\n\n2 Likes\n\nAndrea_Groblin April 13, 2025, 12:31pm 5\n\nThank you so much!\n\n1 Like\n\nmohamed3nan April 13, 2025, 1:58pm 6\n\nThank you, very usefull!\n\n1 Like\n\nharsh.painter April 13, 2025, 7:29pm 7\n\n@data.popcorn very useful. thank you\n\n1 Like\n\nhsteph April 13, 2025, 8:34pm 8\n\nWell done !\n\n1 Like\n\ndata.popcorn April 14, 2025, 12:04pm 9\n\nI wasn’t able to edit the last post, so here’s a better version I just uploaded.\n\n13 Likes\n\nmohamed3nan April 14, 2025, 12:53pm 10\n\nThank you so much,\n\nWhat is the app used to create the cards?\n\nheadset907 April 14, 2025, 6:40pm 11\n\ndata.popcorn April 14, 2025, 10:22pm 12\n\nThe initial version was made with Canva, and later moved to Figma.\n\n2 Likes\n\npsmin91 April 15, 2025, 6:09am 13\n\nVery Nice​:laughing:\n\nEd_P April 18, 2025, 3:24pm 14\n\nThis is what I saw earlier today on LinkedIn.\n\nWondering, who’s copying whom\n\n3 Likes\n\nadrianno April 18, 2025, 4:55pm 15\n\nNice Work - thanks for sharing!\n\nKamil_ulupinar April 20, 2025, 4:53pm 16\n\nThank you! I was really looking for the short cuts and how to customise them… couldn’t find it. Where do you set the short cuts?\n\nmohamed3nan April 22, 2025, 3:08am 17\n\nThe original author is@data.popcorn\n\nI commented on that dishonest LinkedIn guy’s post, asking him to either admit it or give credit to the original creator.\n\nHe deleted my comment and blocked me once people started noticing it\n\n6 Likes\n\ndata.popcorn April 22, 2025, 5:32am 18\n\nThank you so much for letting me know!\n\n2 Likes\n\nIdriss_AGOUMI April 22, 2025, 7:25am 19\n\nThanks! Very useful!\n\n1 Like\n\nBastianHammer April 23, 2025, 11:55am 20\n\nThanks, that looks very good and structured!\n\n---\n\nTitle: n8n Cheat Sheet - DevSheets\nURL: https://devsheets.io/sheets/n8n\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nn8n Cheat Sheet\n...\nn8n workflow automation cheat sheet with nodes, expressions, triggers, code patterns, error handling, and self-hosting deployment tips.\n...\n### Table of Contents\n...\n## Core Concepts\n...\n### Workflows & Nodes\n...\nBasic building blocks of n8n automation\n...\n🎯 Use core nodes (IF, Merge\n...\n## Expression Syntax\n...\n### Accessing Data\n...\n💡 Use $json for inline expressions, $input for Code nodes\n...\n### Date & Time with Luxon\n...\n### Data Transformation\n...\n## Essential Nodes\n...\n### HTTP Request\n...\n### IF & Switch\n...\nUse Switch node instead of nested IF nodes\n...\n### Edit Fields (Set)\n...\n### Merge & Aggregate\n...\n## Code Node\n...\n### JavaScript Patterns\n...\n⚠️ MUST return { json: {...} } - not raw objects!\n...\n### Static Data & Workflow Variables\n...\n## Triggers\n...\n### Webhook Trigger\n...\n### Schedule Trigger\n...\nUse crontab.guru to generate cron expressions\n...\n## Error Handling\n...\n### Error Handling Patterns\n...\n## Self-Hosting\n...\n### Docker Deployment\n...\n### Environment Variables\n...\n## Scaling & Performance\n...\n### Queue Mode\n...\n### Performance Tips\n...\n## Common Gotchas\n...\n## AI Features\n\n---\n\nTitle: N8N Cheat Sheet: Kumud Rudraraju | PDF | Keyboard Shortcut | Artificial Intelligence\nURL: https://www.scribd.com/document/1006627047/n8n\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThe document is a cheat sheet for n8n, covering triggers, nodes, AI agents, HTTP requests, Docker setup, and keyboard shortcuts. It provides a quick reference for starting workflows, using built-in nodes, managing error handling, and utilizing expressions. Additionally, it includes instructions for self-hosting with Docker and various keyboard shortcuts for workflow control and navigation.\n...\nThe document is a cheat sheet for n8n, covering triggers, nodes, AI agents, HTTP requests, Docker setup, and keyboard shortcuts. It provides a quick reference for starting workflows, using built-in nodes, managing error handling, and utilizing expressions. Additionally, it includes instructions for self-hosting with Docker and various keyboard shortcuts for workflow control and navigation.\n...\nN8N CHEATSHEETYour quick guide to triggers, nodes, AIagents, HTTP requests, Docker setup,shortcuts, and more. Kumud Rudraraju\n...\nGETTING STARTED WITH TRIGGERS Get Fake Sample Data\n...\n## Trigger nodes start your workflow when a\n...\nBUILD-IN NODES This table lists trigger and core nodes used to build, control, and automate workflow processes.\n...\nManual because the user starts the workflowTrigger Nodes manually. Ideal for cron-like automations at Schedule fixed intervals. Triggers when a user submits form Form data, useful for lead capture or surveys. Listens for external HTTP requests, Webhook great for integrating with other apps or services.\n...\n## IF Branches flow using conditions.\n...\n## Loop Executes nodes repeatedly.\n...\n## NODES COMMOM SETTING\n...\n## Error Handling On Error: Stop Stops the entire workflow when an\n...\n## Continues to the next node even if\n...\n## On Error: Continue Passes the error info to the next\n...\nUSING EXPRESSIONS Type Expression\n...\n## built-in methods $jmespath(), $fromAI(), $max(),\n...\n## $execution, $itemIndex, $input,\n...\nDOCKER SELF-HOSTING# Install n8n docker\n...\n# Docker Run Kumud Rudraraju\n...\nHTTP REQUESTS(API)cURL Command:\n...\n## Purpose of the Request: This cURL command sends a\n...\nPOST request to an API endpoint to create or submit user data in JSON format. What the API Returns: The API processes the request and returns a response indicating success or failure, along with relevant data or messages. Kumud Rudraraju\n...\nKEYBOARD SHORT-CUT Category Details Shortcut\n...\n## Workflow Control Create New Workflow Ctrl + Alt + N\n...\n## Workflow Control Open Workflow Ctrl + O\n...\n## Workflow Control Save Current Workflow Ctrl + S\n...\n## Workflow Control Run Workflow Ctrl + Enter\n...\n## Workflow Control Undo Ctrl + Z\n...\n## Workflow Control Redo Ctrl + Shift + Z\n...\n## Canvas Nodes Select All Nodes Ctrl + A\n...\n## Canvas Nodes Paste Nodes Ctrl + V\n...\nLeft Mouse +\n...\n## Canvas Zoom Zoom In + or =\n\n---\n\nTitle: n8n Cheat Sheet Dashboard\nURL: https://openerpsolutions.co.uk/n8n_cheetsheet.html\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nn8n Cheat Sheet Dashboard\n...\nDocker Self-Hosting Keyboard Shortcuts Getting Started (Triggers) Expressions Built-in Nodes AI Agent HTTP Request (API) Nodes Common Settings Core Nodes Workflows n8n Hints & Tips Data Transformation & Nodes Database Lookup & Looping Authentication & Credentials Community & Resources Advanced Error Handling Sub-Workflows & Reusability Security & Hardening Community & Resources Workflow Diagram\n...\nn8n Hints & Tips\n...\nof default shortcuts you can use\n...\nin n8n:\n...\n| Category |\n...\n|\n| --- | --- | --- |\n...\nAlt + N |\n| Open Workflow | Ctrl + O |\n| Save Current Workflow | Ctrl + S |\n| Undo | Ctrl + Z |\n| Redo | Ctrl + Shift + Z |\n| Run Workflow | Ctrl + Enter |\n| Stop Workflow | Alt + S |\n| Canvas Zoom | Zoom In | + |\n| Zoom Out | - |\n| Reset Zoom | 0 |\n| Fit Workflow to View | 1 |\n| Zoom In/Out | Ctrl + Mouse Wheel |\n| Canvas Navigation | Move Node (View) | Ctrl + Left Mouse + Drag |\n| Move Node (View) | Middle Mouse + Drag |\n| Move Node (View) | Space + Drag |\n| Move Node (View) | Two Fingers (Touch) |\n| Canvas Nodes | Select All Nodes | Ctrl + A |\n| Copy Node(s) | Ctrl + C |\n| Paste Node(s) | Ctrl + V |\n| Delete Node(s) | Delete |\n| Disable / Enable Node | Ctrl + K / Ctrl + E |\n...\nGetting Started with Triggers\n...\n| Type | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| Manual Trigger\n...\nExecute Workflow” in n8n UI to run workflow immediately |\n| Schedule Trigger | Define CRON expression or time intervals for auto runs |\n| Webhook Trigger | Waits for an HTTP request, runs with the request’s data |\n...\nBuilt-in Nodes\n...\n| Category |\n...\nName | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n...\n| Trigger Node | Manual, Schedule, Webhook... | Start or schedule\n...\nexecution |\n| Core Node | Function | Run custom JS code to manipulate data |\n| Core Node | HTTP Request | Make REST or API calls |\n| Data Transform | Edit Fields | Add/modify fields in incoming data |\n| Data Transform | Filter | Remove items that don’t meet certain conditions |\n| Data Transform | Merge | Combine data from two different sources |\n| Data Transform | Split In Batches | Chunk incoming items into smaller batches |\n| File Operations | Read Binary File | Load file data as binary |\n| File Operations | Write Binary File | Write binary data to disk |\n| Utility | Stop And Error | Intentionally stop the workflow or throw an error |\n...\nSub-Workflows & Reusability\n...\nCore Nodes Workflows\n...\n1) Schedule → Function → HTTP Request\n...\nn8n Hints & Tips\n...\nData Transformation & Nodes\n...\nmerged before being delivered to the final destination.\n...\nDatabase Lookup, Replace Function & Looping\n...\nTriggers & Webhook Responses\n...\nThis section explains how n\n...\nrespond to HTTP requests\n...\nwebhooks.\n...\nsupports several trigger\n\n---\n\nTitle: N8N Cheatsheet | Tha-Shed!!!\nURL: https://tha-shed.com/n8n-cheatsheet/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: Educator September 6, 2025\nHighlights:\nN8N Cheatsheet | Tha-Shed!!!\n...\n## 🔹 𝐂𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐂𝐨𝐧𝐜𝐞𝐩𝐭𝐬\n...\n• Nodes = building blocks (APIs, logic, files)• Workflows = directed graphs of nodes• Items = rows/records flowing through nodes (array of JSONs)• Binary Data = files that travel with items• Triggers = start workflows (e.g., Webhook, Cron)• Executions = individual runs (view logs/data)• Credentials = encrypted API keys & logins• Error Workflows = catch-all for failures\n...\n## 🔹 𝐏𝐨𝐩𝐮𝐥𝐚𝐫\n...\n𝐫𝐢𝐠𝐠𝐞𝐫𝐬\n...\n➤ Webhook – start via HTTP request (great for inbound alerts)➤ Cron / Interval – scheduled jobs (hourly/daily/weekly)➤ IMAP Email – react to new emails➤ Polling – check APIs on a cadence➤ Event/WebSocket – react to external events (where supported)\n...\n## 🔹 𝐄𝐬𝐬𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐢𝐚𝐥 𝐍𝐨𝐝𝐞𝐬\n...\n• HTTP Request – call any REST API• Set – add/rename fields; create constants• If / Switch – conditional routing• Merge – combine branches (by index, key, or append)• SplitInBatches – process large lists safely• Function / Code – custom JS transforms• Wait – delays, windows, backoff• Spreadsheet File – CSV/Excel parse/build• Database – Postgres/MySQL/SQLite queries• Execute Command – run CLI (air-gapped or local ops)\n...\n## 🔹 𝐒𝐜𝐚𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐠 & 𝐇𝐀\n...\nUI+executions•\n...\nUI/scheduler\n...\n+ multiple workers\n...\nRedis; scale\n...\nn8n\n...\nmounted volumes,\n...\n## 🔹 𝐂𝐋𝐈 (𝐊𝐧𝐨𝐰-𝐁𝐲-𝐇𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭)\n...\n```\nn8n start\nn8n import:workflow --input=myflow.json\nn8n export:workflow --id=123 --output=myflow.json\nn8n export:credentials --all --output=creds.json\nn8n user-management:reset   # reset owner/admin\n\n```\n...\n## 🔹 𝐂𝐨𝐦𝐦𝐨𝐧 𝐋𝐨𝐨𝐩𝐬 & 𝐏𝐚𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 (𝐏𝐚𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐧)\n...\n1. HTTP Request (page=1) → 2) IF (has next?) → 3) Merge (append)Use Set/Function to bump`page` param; Wait for backoff.\n...\n𝐫𝐢𝐭\n...\n𝐀𝐮𝐭𝐨𝐦𝐚𝐭\n...\n## 🔹 𝐁𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐏𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐜𝐞𝐬 (𝐏\n...\nfor reuse✔ Version workflows\n...\nGit)✔\n...\nnaming:`team-\n...\ne.g.,`\n...\n## 🔹 𝐀𝐝𝐯𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞𝐝\n...\n• Reusable/Sub-Workflows via Execute Workflow node• Webhook Auth (HMAC headers / shared secrets)• Queues: main + N workers (`EXECUTIONS_MODE=queue`)• Git Sync (export/import flows in CI)• Files/Binary: Move Binary Data ↔ Spreadsheet File ↔ S3• Data Warehousing: Postgres/MySQL nodes → ELT into warehouse• Prompt/AI: call LLM APIs via HTTP; cache with DB; audit outputs\n\n---\n\nTitle: Kookylo/n8n-ultimate-cheat-sheet\nURL: https://github.com/Kookylo/n8n-ultimate-cheat-sheet\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nN8N cheat sheet 500+ functions and examples with copy-paste ready code examples\n...\n# 🚀 n8n Ultimate Cheat Sheet - Interactive Reference\n\n \n\n**The most comprehensive interactive reference for n8n expressions & functions**\n...\nStop searching through documentation! This interactive cheat sheet contains **everything** you need to master n8n expressions:\n...\n- 🎯 **500+ Real Examples** - Copy, paste, and go!\n- 🛡️ **Error-Safe Patterns** - Avoid common pitfalls\n- 🚀 **Performance Tips** - Write faster workflows\n- 📱 **Mobile Friendly** - Reference anywhere\n- 🔍 **Searchable** - Find functions instantly\n- 📋 **Copy-Paste Ready** - Every example is functional\n\n## 🎉 Features\n...\n- **Basic Data Access** - Get fields, access nodes, work with JSON\n- **Date & Time Functions** - Format dates, calculate differences\n- **String Manipulation** - Transform text, extract data, validation\n- **Array Processing** - Filter, map, reduce, sort data lists\n- **Conditional Logic** - IF/THEN statements, complex conditions\n- **Mathematical Operations** - Calculations, statistics, formulas\n- **Object Manipulation** - Build objects, merge data\n- **Multi-Node Data** - Combine data from multiple workflow steps\n- **Error Handling** - Prevent errors, safe access, defaults\n- **Advanced Patterns** - Complex transformations, regex\n- **API & HTTP Helpers** - URL building, headers, authentication\n- **Real-World Examples** - User management, e-commerce, data processing\n\n### 🔥 Interactive Features\n...\n- **One-Click Copy** - Copy any code example instantly\n- **Live Search** - Search 500+ functions and examples\n- **Collapsible Sections** - Organized accordion interface\n- **Difficulty Filtering** - Filter by Beginner/Intermediate/Advanced\n- **Mobile Responsive** - Perfect on any device\n...\n## 🚀 Quick Start Examples\n...\n```javascript\n{{ $json.fieldName }}\n...\nGet field from current item\n...\n{{ $('Node Name').item.json.field }}     // Data from specific node\n...\n{{ $json.items?.[0] }}                   // Safe array access\n...\n.diff('\n...\n### String Manipulation\n...\n### Array Processing\n...\n```javascript\n{{ $json.items.length }}                 // Count array items\n{{ $json.items.filter(item => item.active) }}   // Filter items\n{{ $json.items.map(item => item.name) }}        // Extract field from all items\n...\n- [📚 n8n Official Documentation](https://docs.n8n.io/)\n- [💬 n8n Community Forum](https://community.n8n.io/)\n- [🎯 n8n Workflow Templates](https://n8n.io/workflows/)\n- [🛠️ n8n GitHub Repository](https://github.com/n8n-io/n8n)\n...\n- **Functions Covered:** 500+\n- **Categories:** 12+\n- **Real-World Examples:** 100+\n- **Copy-Paste Ready:** 100%\n- **Mobile Friendly:** ✅\n- **Searchable:** ✅\n\n---\n\nTitle: n8n Cheat Sheet and Workflow Guide | PDF - Scribd\nURL: https://www.scribd.com/document/883402191/n8n-Cheat-Sheet\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nClient Challenge\n\nA required part of this site couldn’t load. This may be due to a browser extension, network issues, or browser settings. Please check your connection, disable any ad blockers, or try using a different browser.",
