      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Yes — it's basically a penetration testing cheat sheet for your own site. Specifically it tells an attacker:\n\n- **Every endpoint** and what it does\n- **Which ones have no auth** (`submit-booking`: \"None (add later)\")\n- **Admin panel path** (`/admin.html`)\n- **Odoo XML-RPC integration** details\n- **Environment variable names** to look for in dumps\n\n**What to do:**\n\n1. **Strip the README** — keep it to one paragraph: what AKcloud is, how to run locally\n2. **Move detailed docs** to a private file (not tracked in git) or a private repo\n3. **Add auth to `submit-booking`** before it goes live — it's your Odoo proxy\n\nWant me to rewrite the README to be safe?",
