      "type": "user-query",
      "text": "yeah but i need to impresss him:\n\n\n\nAI Solutions Consultant / Automation Engineer — Application\nThanks for your interest in joining AI Academy. This takes about 4 minutes. The most useful thing you can share is a link to something you've actually built.\nThe role: AI Solutions Consultant / Automation Engineer (Client-Facing) \nSince 2017, AI Academy has helped thousands of individuals and companies put AI to work through hands-on, project-based programs built around one idea: the best way to learn is to build something real.\n\nAlong the way, we've helped thousands of people learn how, where, and when to use AI, and apply it immediately. Today, we run programs across the US, Europe, Asia, and the Middle East, partnering with global corporations that value our approach and get tangible results out of it.\n\nAs AI changes, so do we.\n\nThe tools are at such a practical level that we are able to help anyone build solutions quickly without compromising the quality of the output. Our client network is now asking for a partner who rolls up their sleeves and builds the custom solutions WITH them, having their teams work with people who understand their complex problems and find creative solutions. Now, we're expanding the team to do exactly that.\n\nHere is a quick example of one of the latest projects we've worked on:\n\nA US pharma company's finance team was burning 60+ hours every quarter manually working on supplier rebate invoices, arriving in more than a dozen different formats, into one spreadsheet.\n\nIn under two months, we helped their team build an AI agent that reads any layout, extracts the data, runs hard checks on the numbers, files it, and flags anything it can't fully trust, successfully and securely. \n\nToday, they've eliminated both those manual hours and the compliance fines that came with them.\n\n👉 That is the kind of project you'd own end-to-end. If your idea of a good time is turning a problem like that into something that works, keep reading because this one is for you.\n\nAbout you\n\nFluent in automation platforms. Strong with n8n, Make, or similar, and you know how to pick the right tool for the job.\n\nExperienced in client-facing delivery. You've scoped and run software projects directly with B2B clients and owned that relationship.\n\nA practical and creative problem-solver. You have a solution proposal to every problem, not the other way around.\n\nA clear communicator. Fluent in English. You make complex work simple and handle client feedback constructively.\n\nProactive. You spot what needs doing and drive it forward independently, take ownership, and adapt when needed.\n\nWhat you will do\n\nOwn AI and automation projects end-to-end, from the first scoping call to delivery.\n\nTurn problems into plans. Scope the need, define a clear execution plan, and keep delivery on track.\n\nBuild and manage automations. Design and ship AI workflows that solve problems.\n\nPresent with confidence. Explain your reasoning, handle questions and pushback, and keep clients aligned.\n\nCollaborate on delivery. Work closely with the client and the team.\n\nSupport training. Occasionally, lend your hands-on credibility to a workshop or session.\n\nTechnical skills we value\n\nCore: n8n / Make or equivalent platforms · No-code and low-code automation · AI workflow and agent tooling · Advanced prompting · Claude workflows and advanced Claude usage · PowerAutomate\n\nNice to have: Copilot Studio · teaching or facilitation experience · applied AI project environments\n\nHiring process\nWe respect the time you will put into this, you can expect a hands-on process with a lot of space for you to show how you approach problems. The process will be as crisp as possible, honest, including feedback. We are open to all questions you might have for us.\n- Intro Call: we get to know your background, experience, and what drives you.\n- Take-home exercise: a practical automation challenge built on an anonymized client project, so you can show how you think, structure, and build.\n- Presentation: you walk us through your solution the way you would with a client.\n- Live working session: a collaborative session with the team you'd be working with, solving a simple problem together.\n- Final call: alignment on expectations, compensation, and next steps.\nCompensation & contract\nFreelance, full-time · Remote (EU-time zone friendly) · €45K–€60K/year depending on experience and location · Preference is for a freelancer contract with a personal company and a valid VAT number.\nFull name\n*\nYour name\nEmail\n*\nyou@email.com\nWhere are you based?\n*\ne.g. Milan, Italy\nLinkedIn profile\n*\nhttps://linkedin.com/in/...\nLinks to your work\n*\nPortfolio, repos, live demos of automations or agents you've built. One per line.\nYour CV\n*\nNo file chosen\nClick to choose a file or drag here\nLink to a presentation or demo video (optional)\nhttps://...\nTell us about one automation you built end to end, and the problem it solved\n*\nA few lines is plenty. What was the problem, what did you build, what changed?\nWhich platforms are you fluent in?\n*\nWhich platforms are you fluent in?\n\nn8n\n\nMake\n\nPower Automate\n\nCopilot Studio\n\nZapier\n\nClaude Cowork / advanced Claude\n\nCodex\n\nOther\nAre you comfortable owning B2B client relationships?\n*\nAre you comfortable owning B2B client relationships?\nA\n\nYes, I've done it\nB\n\nSome experience\nC\n\nNot yet, but keen\nEarliest you could start\ne.g. immediately, or 1 month notice\nHow did you hear about this role?\n\nSubmit application\n",
