      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\AKcloud\\akcloud-deploy\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AKcloud — Coming Soon Site\n2: \n3: Sovereign-cloud landing page for AKcloud / AndieKobbieTech. Static-first, with a small backend on Netlify for real lead capture and future Odoo integration.\n4: \n5: ## Stack\n6: \n7: - **Frontend**: Plain HTML + CSS + vanilla JS (no build step)\n8: - **Hosting**: Netlify (static)\n9: - **Forms**: Netlify Forms (`data-netlify=\"true\"`)\n10: - **Functions**: Netlify Functions (serverless, Node 18+)\n11: - **Email**: Resend (optional, via Function webhook)\n12: - **Booking backend**: Odoo (eventually sovereign on OCI + Elestio)\n13: \n14: ## Local dev\n15: \n16: ```powershell\n17: # Install Netlify CLI for local Functions testing\n18: npm install -g netlify-cli\n19: \n20: # Start local dev server (functions + site together)\n21: netlify dev\n22: ```\n23: \n24: Then open http://localhost:8888\n25: \n26: ## Deploy\n27: \n28: ### Option A — Connect to GitHub (recommended for ongoing work)\n29: \n30: 1. Push this folder to a new GitHub repo\n31: 2. Netlify dashboard → **Add new site → Import existing project** → pick the repo\n32: 3. Build settings: leave defaults (no build command, publish directory = `.`)\n33: 4. Click **Deploy site**\n34: \n35: Every push redeploys automatically. PRs get preview URLs.\n36: \n37: ### Option B — Drag-and-drop\n38: \n39: Drag this folder onto https://app.netlify.com/drop. Live in 30 seconds.\n40: \n41: ## Functions\n42: \n43: | Path | Purpose | Auth |\n44: |---|---|---|\n45: | `/.netlify/functions/health` | Health check + deploy info | None |\n46: | `/.netlify/functions/notify-signup` | Receives form-submission webhooks; logs, emails, Slack | Netlify-internal |\n47: | `/.netlify/functions/get-waitlist` | Returns recent submissions as JSON for admin | Basic auth |\n48: | `/.netlify/functions/submit-booking` | Proxies bookings to sovereign Odoo via XML-RPC | None (add later) |\n49: \n50: The `/api/*` path is rewired to `/.netlify/functions/*` in `netlify.toml`.\n51: \n52: ## Environment variables\n53: \n54: Set these in **Netlify dashboard → Site settings → Environment variables**:\n55: \n56: | Variable | Required for | Notes |\n57: |---|---|---|\n58: | `RESEND_API_KEY` | Email notifications | From resend.com |\n59: | `NOTIFY_EMAIL` | Email notifications | Where signup emails go |\n60: | `SLACK_WEBHOOK` | Slack/Discord alerts | Optional |\n61: | `ADMIN_USER` | `/api/get-waitlist` | Pick a strong username |\n62: | `ADMIN_PASS` | `/api/get-waitlist` | Pick a strong password |\n63: | `NETLIFY_SITE_ID` | `/api/get-waitlist` | From API access token |\n64: | `NETLIFY_API_TOKEN` | `/api/get-waitlist` | Personal access token from Netlify |\n65: | `ODOO_URL` | `/api/submit-booking` | https://your-sovereign-odoo.example.com |\n66: | `ODOO_DB` | `/api/submit-booking` | DB name |\n67: | `ODOO_USER` | `/api/submit-booking` | API user email |\n68: | `ODOO_API_KEY` | `/api/submit-booking` | From Odoo → User → API Keys |\n69: \n70: ## Security\n71: \n72: - All HTML has `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `nosniff`, `HSTS`, `Referrer-Policy`\n73: - `/admin.html` is `noindex, nofollow`\n74: - Turn on **Visitor access password protection** in Netlify dashboard for `/admin`\n75: - HSTS preload submitted — register at https://hstspreload.org once you're sure\n76: \n77: ## Roadmap\n78: \n79: - [x] Static landing page deployed to Netlify\n80: - [x] Netlify Forms for the email signup\n81: - [x] Functions for notification + admin API + Odoo proxy\n82: - [ ] Sovereign Odoo on OCI Always Free via Elestio (separate project)\n83: - [ ] Switch `/api/submit-booking` from Odoo Online Free → sovereign OCI Odoo\n84: - [ ] Replace localStorage waitlist with Netlify Forms API view in admin.html\n85: \n86: See `odoo-sovereign-deploy-guide.md` in `Documents\\AKcloud\\` for the OCI + Elestio deployment walkthrough.\n\n(End of file - total 86 lines)\n</content>",
