      "text": "**Assessment — here's what's public and what's safe:**\n\n| File | Risk | What it reveals |\n|---|---|---|\n| `README.md` | ✅ Safe | Clean portfolio piece |\n| `netlify.toml` | ⚠️ Low | API redirect pattern `/api/* → functions`, but no secrets |\n| `admin.html` | ⚠️ Medium | Shows admin panel exists, stores config in **localStorage** (not hardcoded) |\n| `submit-booking.js` | ✅ Safe | Uses `process.env` for all secrets — no hardcoded values |\n| `get-waitlist.js` | ✅ Safe | Uses `process.env` for tokens |\n| `index.html` | ✅ Safe | Just the landing page |\n\n**What an attacker learns:**\n- Admin panel at `/admin.html`\n- API proxy pattern exists\n- Odoo integration exists\n- Functions exist\n\n**What they CAN'T learn from the code:**\n- No API keys, passwords, or tokens (all in Netlify env vars)\n- No hardcoded Odoo credentials\n- localStorage config is empty by default\n\n**One thing to fix:** The `admin.html` auth guard is client-side only (sessionStorage check). Anyone can view-source and see how it works. But since the real data comes from serverless functions with env-var auth, this is **low risk**.\n\n**Bottom line:** You're fine. No secrets are exposed. The README is now a clean portfolio piece. Want me to add anything else to impress AI Academy?",
