      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I understand the admin.html waitlist implementation. It currently only reads from localStorage. I need to add a function that fetches from the get-waitlist serverless function and merges the results.\n\nThe get-waitlist function requires basic auth (ADMIN_USER + ADMIN_PASS env vars). The admin.html would need to prompt for these credentials or store them in localStorage.\n\nLet me update the admin.html to:\n1. Add a function to fetch from the get-waitlist API\n2. Merge the API results with localStorage data\n3. Update the init to try fetching from the API first\n\nLet me also check the booking widget issue. Looking at the index.html code:\n- When `ak_booking_url` is set in localStorage, it opens that URL directly\n- When not set, it shows the notify-me form\n\nThe submit-booking function exists but isn't used. The current behavior is actually fine for the use case - when Odoo is configured, open the Odoo booking page directly. The submit-booking function is a proxy for when you want to submit bookings through the serverless function instead.\n\nLet me focus on fixing the admin waitlist first, then decide if the booking widget needs changes.",
      "timestamp": 1782288726475
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "edit",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Documents\\\\AKcloud\\\\akcloud-deploy\\\\admin.html\", \"oldString\": \"  // \\u2500\\u2500 WAITLIST \\u2500\\u2500\\n  function getWaitlist() {\\n    try { return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('ak_notify_list') || '[]'); } catch { return []; }\\n  }\", \"newString\": \"  // \\u2500\\u2500 WAITLIST \\u2500\\u2500\\n  function getWaitlistLocal() {\\n    try { return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('ak_notify_list') || '[]'); } catch { return []; }\\n  }\\n\\n  async function fetchWaitlistRemote() {\\n    const user = localStorage.getItem('ak_admin_user') || '';\\n    const pass = localStorage.getItem('ak_admin_pass') || '';\\n    if (!user || !pass) return null;\\n    try {\\n      const res = await fetch('/api/get-waitlist', {\\n        headers: { 'Authorization': 'Basic ' + btoa(user + ':' + pass) }\\n      });\\n      if (!res.ok) return null;\\n      const data = await res.json();\\n      return data.submissions || [];\\n    } catch { return null; }\\n  }\\n\\n  async function getWaitlist() {\\n    const local = getWaitlistLocal();\\n    const remote = await fetchWaitlistRemote();\\n    if (!remote) return local;\\n    const seen = new Set(local.map(e => (typeof e === 'string' ? e : e.email)));\\n    const merged = [...local];\\n    remote.forEach(e => {\\n      const email = e.email || '';\\n      if (email && !seen.has(email)) {\\n        merged.push({ email, ts: e.created_at ? new Date(e.created_at).getTime() : null, source: 'netlify' });\\n        seen.add(email);\\n      }\\n    });\\n    return merged;\\n  }\"}",
      "output": "Edit applied successfully.",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1782288733250
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I need to update the refreshWaitlist, clearWaitlist, and init functions to work with the async getWaitlist function.",
