    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now for the booking widget. Looking at the current behavior:\n\n1. When `ak_booking_url` is set in localStorage → opens that URL directly (Odoo booking page)\n2. When not set → shows \"Notify Me at Launch\" form\n\nThe submit-booking function exists but isn't used. The current behavior is actually reasonable - when Odoo is configured, it opens the Odoo booking page directly. The submit-booking function is a proxy for when you want to submit bookings through the serverless function instead.\n\nHowever, the README claims \"Appointment booking system integrated with Odoo backend via XML-RPC\" which implies the booking goes through the serverless proxy. Let me update the booking widget to use the submit-booking function when a form is submitted.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the code, the booking modal shows a \"Notify Me at Launch\" form, not an actual booking form. The submit-booking function expects appointment_type_id, datetime, name, email, phone - but the current form only collects email.\n\nI think the best approach is to keep the current behavior (open Odoo directly when configured) but also add a fallback that uses the submit-booking function when the user submits the notify-me form. This way:\n1. When Odoo is configured → opens Odoo booking page\n2. When not configured → shows notify-me form → submits to Netlify Forms AND calls submit-booking function\n\nActually, that doesn't make sense either. The submit-booking function creates a calendar.event in Odoo, but the notify-me form is just collecting emails for later notification.\n\nLet me reconsider. The booking widget has two modes:\n1. Odoo configured → open Odoo booking page directly\n2. Not configured → collect email for notification\n\nThe submit-booking function is for a future integration where users can book directly through the site. For now, the current behavior is correct.\n\nBut the README claims \"Appointment booking system integrated with Odoo backend via XML-RPC\" which is technically true - the function exists and is ready to use. The booking widget just doesn't use it yet because it's in \"notify me\" mode.\n\nI think the best fix is to update the README to be more accurate about what's implemented, rather than changing the booking widget behavior. But the user asked me to fix gaps, so let me think about what makes sense.\n\nActually, looking at the index.html more carefully, the booking modal collects email via the notify form. When the user submits, it saves to localStorage and submits to Netlify Forms. The submit-booking function is separate - it's for when you have a full booking form with name, email, datetime, appointment_type_id.\n\nI think the right approach is:\n1. Keep the current booking widget behavior as-is\n2. Note in the README that the submit-booking function is ready for future integration\n3. Or, add a simple booking form that uses the submit-booking function\n\nLet me just note this as a \"ready for integration\" item rather than changing the behavior, since the current flow makes sense for a \"coming soon\" page.\n\nActually, let me just skip this fix since the current behavior is intentional - the booking widget shows \"Notify Me\" when Odoo isn't configured, and opens Odoo directly when it is. The submit-booking function is a serverless proxy that's ready for when they want to build a full booking form.\n\nLet me update the README to be more accurate and commit everything.",
