      "text": "Now I need to commit and tell the user to push. The config.json approach means:\n1. The booking URL is stored in a JSON file in the repo\n2. The frontend fetches it from config.json\n3. It's cached in localStorage for performance\n4. To change it, the user edits config.json and pushes to GitHub\n\nBut wait, the user wants to be able to edit it via the admin panel. The current approach requires editing the file manually. Let me think about this...\n\nActually, the user can edit config.json locally and push to GitHub. The admin panel can show the current URL and provide instructions. But it can't save back to the file without a backend.\n\nFor now, this is the simplest solution that works. Let me commit and explain.",
