    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Here's how it works now:\n\n1. **`config.json`** in your repo holds the booking URL\n2. **First visit**: fetches from `config.json`, caches in localStorage\n3. **Return visits**: uses cached localStorage (fast)\n4. **All visitors**: get the URL from `config.json` on first load\n\n**To change the URL:**\n1. Edit `config.json` locally\n2. Push to GitHub\n3. All visitors get the new URL on their next visit\n\n**To push:**\n```\ngit push --force\n```\n\n**Limitation:** The admin panel can't save back to `config.json` without a backend. To change the URL, edit the file manually and push. When Netlify credits refresh, I can add a serverless function that saves it.",
      "timestamp": 1782290990219
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Done. Let me explain the solution to the user.",
      "timestamp": 1782290998505
    },
    {
      "type": "user-query",
      "text": "can i not add a servless function rn then?",
